---            ---
--OpenCalc 0.0_3--
---            ---

OpenCalc is terminal based open-source calculator for GNU/Linux.


Instruction Manual:

Four options available in this version for calculating.

(1) for addition,
(2) for subtraction,
(3) for multiplication,
(4) for division.

Please type 1, 2, 3 or 4 number for selecting calculating method and calculate anything you want.
You can only calculate two number in this version. We working to solve this problem in ver-0_4.


--Installation--

make - (for compiling binary file. (After compiling binary file will be moved to bin directory.))

make install - (for installing software to /usr/bin.)

make clean - (for removing bin/opencalc.)

make uninstall - (for uninstalling software from /usr/bin.)


- For installing this software, enter this commands:

make && sudo make install

- For uninstalling this software, enter this commands:

make clean && sudo make uninstall


